specialize the shared reconcile path while
explicit gaps still block generated promotion.
service: database
slug: autonomousdatabases
kind: AutonomousDatabases
archetype: legacy-adapter
status/finalizer: manual / none
requeue: provisioning, updating
provider states: create PROVISIONING, STARTING;
update MAINTENANCE_IN_PROGRESS, PROVISIONING,
RESTARTING, SCALE_IN_PROGRESS (+5 more); delete
TERMINATING, UNAVAILABLE
supported drift: admin_password,
are_primary_whitelisted_ips_used,
auto_refresh_frequency_in_seconds,
auto_refresh_point_lag_in_seconds (+107 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
autonomous_container_database_id,
autonomous_database_backup_id,
autonomous_database_id, character_set (+12 more)
and conflicts is_shrink_only ->
shrink_adb_trigger
list lookup: oci_database_autonomous_databases
filters autonomous_container_database_id,
compartment_id, db_version, db_workload (+9
more)
conflicts: is_shrink_only -> shrink_adb_trigger
open gaps: bind-versus-create,
delete-confirmation, legacy-adapter,
list-lookup, manual-webhook (+4 more)
Create first lists by displayName and
compartment before deciding to bind or create.
Wallet secret generation is optional and only
runs after the database is active.
Delete remains an unsupported legacy path, so no
terminating state is confirmed today.
end note
